00:09:21.070 --> 00:09:24.070
I think we need to learn to
read movement code better first.

00:09:24.070 --> 00:09:26.160
And if we can read
that code better,

00:09:26.160 --> 00:09:29.840
I think there are a lot of
brains in the world that just

00:09:29.840 --> 00:09:31.490
have a slight paradigm shift.

00:09:31.490 --> 00:09:33.860
Don't look at me
as a bag of parts.

00:09:33.860 --> 00:09:37.410
Don't tell me that structure
always governs function,

00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:39.860
because it doesn't.

00:09:39.860 --> 00:09:42.510
Structure has a big
influence on function.

00:09:42.510 --> 00:09:44.270
But let me ask you a question.

00:09:44.270 --> 00:09:46.280
Does a right-handed
tennis player

00:09:46.280 --> 00:09:49.474
have twice the bone
density in this forearm

00:09:49.474 --> 00:09:51.140
because they were
born that way and it's

00:09:51.140 --> 00:09:53.014
a good thing they played
tennis on this side?

00:09:53.014 --> 00:09:56.900
Or did the act of squeezing the
crap out of that tennis racket

00:09:56.900 --> 00:10:00.030
at impact create more
compressive forces

00:10:00.030 --> 00:10:03.560
on the bone, which put in action
a thing called Wolff's law

00:10:03.560 --> 00:10:05.750
that adds greater bone
density any time we're

00:10:05.750 --> 00:10:07.224
going to need greater stress.

00:10:07.224 --> 00:10:09.390
You don't just get bigger
muscles when you work out.

00:10:09.390 --> 00:10:12.070
Your bone density goes up.

00:10:12.070 --> 00:10:15.950
So a lot of times,
function governs structure.

00:10:15.950 --> 00:10:18.530
When kids start throwing
really early in their life,

00:10:18.530 --> 00:10:21.430
overhand, they remodel their
entire shoulder mechanics.

00:10:21.430 --> 00:10:23.610
And I can see, when
you're 35 years old

00:10:23.610 --> 00:10:26.431
and haven't picked up
a baseball in 20 years,

00:10:26.431 --> 00:10:27.930
that you through a
lot when you were

00:10:27.930 --> 00:10:33.222
a kid just by the signature
that it left on you.

00:10:33.222 --> 00:10:35.680
We have a little saying in the
clinic when an athlete comes

00:10:35.680 --> 00:10:38.669
through and they've run their
self right into the ground.

00:10:38.669 --> 00:10:40.210
